   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "wRMtsJKBaxWu"
   },
   "source": [
    "## About the dataset\n",
    "Explain what the data is in your own words. What are your features and labels? What is the mapping of your labels to the actual classes?\n",
    "\n",
    "<br> There are 4 features: sepal_length, sepal_width, petal_length, petal_width, and there is one label: species. The 4 features are numerical descriptions of the sizes of the sepal and petal of each flower, and the label tells us what species it is. Our model is going to take in these 4 features which are measurements of the flower and output the MOST LIKELY classification of species for that flower. For each of the labels/species there is exactly one classification which the model can output, so the unique labels comprise the possible classes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "DhKaIrZKNaHg"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Part 2: Split the dataset into train and test"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "OrgogB62NcOi",
    "outputId": "7bbfb1ea-88ed-4944-ab94-48696b9a71df"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(135, 4)\n",
      "(135,)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "# Take the dataset and split it into our features (X) and label (y)\n",
    "features = df.iloc[:,:-1]\n",
    "label = df.iloc[:,-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use sklearn to split the features and labels into a training/test set. (90% train, 10% test)\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(features, label, random_state=42, train_size=0.9)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(X_train.shape)\n",
    "print(y_train.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "hblF-ei9Ncia"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Part 3: Logistic Regression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "IhFhEN03Nf7o",
    "outputId": "15a94661-020b-4520-b5f3-c34fdfb042f2"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Probability of class 'setosa': 0.9601\n",
      "Probability of class 'versicolor': 0.0399\n",
      "Probability of class 'virginica': 0.0000\n",
      "Accuracy score of the Logistic Regression model: 1.0\n",
      "Coefficients: [[-1.06736156  1.15430144 -1.8781162  -1.75288118]\n",
      " [ 0.5348387  -0.27436641 -0.33674998 -0.78754596]\n",
      " [ 0.53252286 -0.87993503  2.21486618  2.54042714]]\n",
      "Intercept: [-0.27430319  2.00354565 -1.72924245]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# 1. Import necessary libraries\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Scale the data\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_train_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X_train) \n",
    "X_test_scaled = scaler.transform(X_test)  \n",
    "\n",
    "# ii. Create a Logistic Regression model and fit it\n",
    "model = LogisticRegression(random_state=42) \n",
    "model.fit(X_train_scaled, y_train)  \n",
    "\n",
    "# iii. For a sample datapoint, predict the probabilities for each possible class\n",
    "sample_df = pd.DataFrame({'sepal_length': [5.4], 'sepal_width' : [3.6], 'petal_length' : [1.9], 'petal_width' : [0.3]})\n",
    "sample_scaled = scaler.transform(sample_df)\n",
    "probabilities = model.predict_proba(sample_scaled)\n",
    "class_labels = model.classes_\n",
    "for prob, label in zip(probabilities[0], class_labels):\n",
    "    print(f\"Probability of class '{label}': {prob:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# iv. Scoring the Logistic Regression model\n",
    "y_pred = model.predict(X_test_scaled)  \n",
    "score = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
    "print(\"Accuracy score of the Logistic Regression model:\", score)\n",
    "\n",
    "# v. Extract the coefficients and intercept\n",
    "coefficients = model.coef_\n",
    "intercept = model.intercept_\n",
    "print(\"Coefficients:\", coefficients)\n",
    "print(\"Intercept:\", intercept)\n"
   ]
  },
